{
  "stem": "26728.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I went from there to Camp Roberts, which is around San Luis Obispo to what they call a replacement-- a repo depo, a replacement place-- they were-- base.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were probably 50-- to 100,000 men in the vicinity of Camp Roberts, in tents again.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All these promises of steam-heated barracks never materialized for me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was one of the promises they made to us when going to Fort Sill.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I never slept in a steam-heated barracks until much later on.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was always a four-man-- a six-man tent.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "At Camp Roberts, I was the cadre again.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then I was assigned to a new camp, Camp Adair in Oregon, Corvallis-- out by Corvallis-- as a cadre man.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I still had my, my-- had passed the test.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I was waiting to be called into the Air Corps.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I had friends in-- family friends who were in-- had been in the military who were-- in World War I, especially-- who were help-- were writing letters to officers in the Air For-- in the Air Corps, trying to help me get in.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because by then, they were taking four-year graduates with engineering degrees.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "See, I didn't have that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I had-- I had two years, and none of it was engineering.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So, if you had a four degree-- a four-year degree with engineering, you were-- and you were qualified otherwise, you were first choice.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So I was way down the ladder, but I didn't know this at the time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I went-- we built the 70th Division, and this was my home division in Oregon here, in 1943.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "From-- and we also were involved with two or three other divisions, which does-- doesn't matter-- all of whom went to Europe.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
